name: lib/index.js
fromPacket
description: Extract service identifier and payload from KNXnet/IP packet.

name: toPacket
description: Generate a Buffer that contains a KNXnet/IP packet with the given service identifier and payload.

throws.description: If payload length exceeds 16-bit unsigned integer upper bound

name: Packet
description:
KNXnet/IP packet

Represents an entire packet, which is structured as follows:

| Octet | Field                   | Description                                               |
|------:|:------------------------|:----------------------------------------------------------|
|     0 | Header structure length | Always 6                                                  |
|     1 | Protocol version        | Always 16                                                 |
| 2 - 3 | Service identifier      | Describes which kind of payload you can expect            |
| 4 - 5 | Entire packet length    | Length of the entire packet, including header and payload |
| 6 - n | Payload                 | Contains the payload that matches the services identifier |

name: fromBuffer
description: Extract a KNXnet/IP packet from the given buffer.

throws.description: If given buffer is too small or its contents are invalid

name: toBuffer
description: Write KNXnet/IP packet including its payload to the given buffer.

params.name: buffer
params.description: Output buffer (allocates an appropriate buffer when omitted)

throws.description: If payload is too large or the given buffer is too small

name: HostInfo
description:
Host information

Represents the `Host Protocol Address Information`, which is structured as follows:

| Octet | Field            | Description                    |
|------:|:-----------------|:-------------------------------|
|     0 | Structure length | Always 8                       |
|     1 | Protocol         | 1 is UDP, 2 is TCP             |
| 2 - 5 | IPv4 address     | Network-ordered representation |
| 6 - 7 | Port number      | Network-ordered representation |

name: fromBuffer
description: Extract a {@link HostInfo} instance from the given buffer and offset.

throws.description: If given buffer is too small or buffer contents are invalid
If given address is not in IPv4 format
